parameters:
\n<Arno>Hmm... I thought you'd be coming around this time. Just as I
expected, more or less♥

\n<Arno>This is the new rental place I've acquired. It was quite a
hassle, you know? After what happened, I certainly couldn't
stay at Lumare Magic Academy anymore.

<Arno>Now, you remember the contract that 
[1] and I made, don't
you? "I will only extract vital energy from 
[1]." "
[1]
cannot attack me."

\n<Arno>This bond is absolute. Even if you wanted to break it, your
soul wouldn't allow it. That's how serious a contract is.

\n<Arno>Hmm, level 1, huh... What to do. Should I dispose of you and
break the contract now...

\n<Arno>No, you will surely come back to me. I can tell. Let's
postpone killing you to another day.

\n<Arno>My mission is to investigate human ecology. To us demons,
humans are an unknown variable after all.

\n<Arno>I might get scolded for saying this, but our current Demon
Lord is a bit of an odd one. Fond of entanglements, or
rather, trying out new things.

\n<Arno>Succubi, as a species, generally have low combat abilities.
We allocate our resources to intelligence. Pure combat
strength is far higher in less intelligent demons.

\n<Arno>We use a method called Energy Drain to siphon strength from
humans, and only then can we fight properly. A low-ranking
succubus has about the same combat power as an average
woman.

\n<Arno>This is a secret, but it seems there are other succubi
besides me assigned to study human ecology. I haven't been
told their names, but it's said to be a very important
mission.

\n<Arno>Just between us, the recent increase in succubi seems to be
because the Hero's weakness was seduction. It's a
ridiculously silly story, isn't it? *chuckle*♥

\n<Arno>Being expelled from the academy was quite troubling, but
fortunately, it seems my issue has been buried in darkness
due to the academy's shallow ego not wanting the scandal
known.

\n<Arno>It's fortunate for me... but humans really are an enigma.
They are foolish creatures that cannot admit their mistakes.

\n<Arno>Oh my, you seem unable to hold back any longer. *chuckle*♥
Are you itching to be stepped on by me?

\n<Arno>I've been waiting for \n[1]. Bound by the contract, they
are the only human I can attack.

\n<Arno>Disguising as a human is quite difficult, you know? Horns
and tails can be left visible because of beastmen, but more
than that, it's hard to suppress the hunger.

\n<Arno>If I were to compare it to something you'd understand...
It's like a roast chicken wearing clothes and talking to
you. It's only natural to get hungry, right?

\n<Arno>\n[1]'s magical power is of very high quality. Could it be
that you're a twin? Such special magic power isn't common.

\n<Arno>Twins are originally one life that for some reason has split
into two. They are beings that slightly stick out from the
logic of this world.

\n<Arno>Basically, the total number of substances and souls in the
world is fixed. It neither decreases nor increases. Twins
are a "glitch" that increases that total number.

\n<Arno>When something unexpected happens, a tremendous amount of
energy is generated. Your exceptional talent is both a gift
bestowed by the world and an anomaly.

\n<Arno>Now then, let us begin our union in accordance with the
contract.\C[14]（Arno Lv\v[707]）

\n<Arno>Ah! You're taking someone's snack...!! Grrr... Can't be
helped, I suppose. Just one, okay?

It's a human ecology survey report. It's organized in a way
that's easy to understand at a glance... I'm a bit
impressed.

\n<Arno>It's explained logically using the PREP method. A method to
convey the main points concisely and clearly. Hehehe. All
that's left is to insert cute illustrations into the empty
spaces.

It's a textbook on barrier magic. There are sticky notes all
over it, almost on every page. It seems there's a lot that's
not well understood.

\n<Arno>Please don't look at that. You see, barrier magic is a
special kind of magic used against monsters. Do you really
think a monster like me could handle it properly?

It's a textbook on advanced magic. It's written about
various types of magic.

\n<Arno>I've finished reading it. The content was indeed
fascinating. Well, I can only use water attribute magic
though.

What is magic? Magic from a scientific standpoint. It seems
to be a book with somewhat difficult content.

\n<Arno>Magic is the extraction of energy through the spiritual
world. Oops, the existence of the spiritual world isn't
widely recognized, is it? But it's something deeply familiar
to us demons.
